1 following:
2 (1) Current tuition, fees, testing costs, cancellation fees, and ancillary charges
3 assessed by licensed driver education providers.
4 (2) Regional differences in pricing throughout Louisiana.
5 (3) Factors contributing to cost increases.
6 (4) Comparative practices used by other states to regulate or support affordability in
7 driver education.
8 (5) Recommendations for legislation or administrative rule changes to increase
9 affordability and regulate pricing.
10 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the office of motor vehicles may consult and
11 collaborate with the Louisiana Legislative Auditor in conducting this study.
12 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the office of motor vehicles shall submit a
13 written report of findings and recommendations to the Senate Committee on Transportation,
14 Highways and Public Works and the Senate President Pro Tempore, and to the David R.
15 Poynter Legislative Research Library as required by R.S. 24:771 and 772, no later than
16 February 1, 2027.
17 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that a copy of this Resolution be transmitted to the
18 commissioner of the office of motor vehicles.
